network.param.config

Interface IReceiptBulkFileImportConfig

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IAttachment, IBulkFileImportConfig
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ReceiptDocumentFileBulkConfig

    public interface IReceiptBulkFileImportConfig
extends IBulkFileImportConfig
    Perform bulk upload receipts XLS into ParamNetwork.

    This interface will help to load/read the XLS receipt file from AWS/Azure/SFTP into the param network.

    Want to perform any bulk imports you need to implement this interface addBulkUpload or addBulkUpload.

    IReceiptBulkFileUploadConfig defines four categories of operations:

    • Based on the config getFileContent will read the file content, if any error while reading this file it will return null, otherwise it will return bytebuffer. addBulkUpload or updateBulkUpload will call while converting XLS into Param internal JSONLD format.

    • Based on the config getSize will return the file size in bytes. This method will be invoked at the time of addBulkUpload or updateBulkUpload for keep track of original size and after reading data from getFileContent(). If both values are different it will throw exception.

    • Based on the config getLastModifiedDate will return file last modified date in bytes. This method will be invoked at the time of addBulkUpload or updateBulkUpload for informational purpose getFileContent().

    • Based on the config getFileExtension will return file extension. addBulkUpload or updateBulkUpload

    • To know data is inward isInward or not, By default its false. . addBulkUpload or updateBulkUpload

    • Based on the config getReceiptDocumentType will return file extension. addBulkUpload or updateBulkUpload

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Jitendra Kumar Balla, ParamNetwork

    • Method Detail

      • isInward

        boolean isInward()
        Return inward true or false.

        Method will return true for reverse flow, Otherwise its regular flow.

        Reverse flow means:
        Seller:
        • Raise PO
        • Init Payment
        Buyer:
        • Create Quotation
        • Raise Invoice
        Returns:
        inward true for reverse flow otherwise false.

      • getReceiptDocumentType

        ReceiptDocumentType getReceiptDocumentType()
        Method returns import ReceiptDocumentType document type.

        This method will invoked by addBulkUpload(IBulkFileUploadConfig) or updateBulkUpload(IBulkFileUploadConfig) or addBulkUpload(IReceiptBulkFileUploadConfig) or updateBulkUpload(IReceiptBulkFileUploadConfig) Based on inward() and getReceiptDocumentType() parsing the data and convert into ParamNetwork JSONLD format and make a transaction.

        Returns:
        ReceiptDocumentType
